7 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT GENERALLY REVISING EDUCATION LAWS; ESTABLISHING A
8 LEGISLATIVE GOAL FOR PUBLIC ELEMENTARY AND SECONDARY SCHOOLS TO SUPPORT
9 INSTRUCTION OF PREVENTION AND AVOIDANCE OF CHILD SEX TRAFFICKING AND HUMAN
10 TRAFFICKING; REQUIRING ENCOURAGING THE OFFICE OF PUBLIC INSTRUCTION TO UNDERTAKE
11 ACTIVITIES TO EDUCATE MONTANANS ABOUT AND PREVENT CHILD SEX TRAFFICKING AND HUMAN
12 TRAFFICKING; AMENDING SECTIONS 20-1-102 AND 20-7-1316, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE
13 DATE.”
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
16
17 Section 1. Section 20-1-102, MCA, is amended to read:
18 "20-1-102. Legislative goals for public elementary and secondary schools. It is the goal of the
19 legislature that Montana's public elementary and secondary school system, in cooperation with parents or
20 guardians, create a learning environment for each student that:
21 (1) develops a sound foundation for literacy and numeracy during the early years that is built upon
22 and reinforced throughout the educational experience;
23 (2) furthers the ability to reason critically, creatively, and strategically;
24 (3) fosters the ability to effectively understand and communicate ideas, knowledge, and thoughts;
25 (4) develops a sense of personal and civic responsibility;
26 (5) provides an in-depth understanding of the American political, social, and economic systems
27 and the historical context from which they arose;
