9
10 Section 2. Section 20-7-1316, MCA, is amended to read:
11 "20-7-1316. Child sex trafficking and human trafficking prevention. The office of public instruction
12 is encouraged to shall is encouraged to undertake activities to educate Montanans about and prevent child sex
13 trafficking and human trafficking. Activities may include but are not limited to:
14 (1) reviewing best practices for preventing child sex trafficking and human trafficking;
15 (2) providing access to educational resources for interested parents, teachers, child-care
16 providers, and other community members on how to prevent child sex trafficking and human trafficking, on the
17 warning signs of child sex trafficking and human trafficking, and on predatory behaviors;
18 (3) coordinating educational and prevention efforts with law enforcement, the department of public
19 health and human services, and local organizations that work to prevent child sex trafficking and human
20 trafficking; and
21 (4) supporting school districts in developing:
22 (a) policies on child sex trafficking and human trafficking awareness, prevention, response, and
23 reporting; and
24 (b) educational materials and curricula aimed at preventing child sex trafficking and human
25 trafficking."
26
27 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Effective date. [This act] is effective July 1, 2025.
